  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0bb7\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b87\u0bb4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Failure of the government to seek Russian assistance is a major crime against the people - Kamanpila",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Energy Minister Udaya Kamanpila has said that the government's failure to seek Russia's help in purchasing fuel is a major crime against the people as the country's fuel supply structure faces a dire crisis.",
        "Wimal Weerawansa, the leader of the National Sumanthira Front, had questioned in parliament on the 22nd that the government was not paying attention to buying cheap fuel from Russia. In response, Energy and Power Minister Kanjana Wijesekera said, \"Your (Wimal Weerawansa) former power minister in the coalition has been in the ministry for the past year and a half. Why did he not get fuel from Russia?\"",
        "I am the only Minister of Power in the Independent Parties and it is clear that I have been indicted without mentioning my name. Therefore, it is necessary for the Minister of Power to clarify the matter.",
        "The war between Russia and Ukraine began on February 24, 2022. European countries began imposing a limited embargo on Russia on February 26. On March 3, the President removed me from the post of Minister of Power. The media coverage is a prime example of the fact that I have repeatedly stated that fuel can be obtained cheaply from Russia.",
        "Opposition leader Sajid Premadasa and current Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe have repeatedly said in the past that the fuel supply structure would face a major crisis in the coming months. However, we were initially able to control the crisis situation on the basis of the long-term debt of India and China's credit facilities.",
        "Russia sees Sri Lanka as the best country to get fuel credit facilities in the current crisis situation. Russia has enough fuel. However, Sri Lanka has not yet held any possible talks to obtain fuel from Russia. It is a heinous crime against the government to ignore the fact that people are waiting in line at the fuel line, even though many have lost their lives."
      ],
